## Best Practices

### Service Design

- Design services with clear boundaries
- Use meaningful message and method names
- Keep proto files organized
- Version your proto files
- Use enums for fixed sets of values

### Performance

- Use streaming for large datasets
- Implement proper pagination
- Set appropriate deadlines
- Use connection pooling
- Enable compression for large messages

### Error Handling

- Use appropriate gRPC status codes
- Include useful error details
- Implement retry logic with exponential backoff
- Use deadlines to prevent hanging requests

### Monitoring

- Log all RPC calls
- Track latency and throughput
- Monitor error rates
- Set up alerts for anomalies
- Use distributed tracing

